Meet the new @mercedesbenz CLE 🤩 The 2023 Coupé and Cabriolet combines the best of both worlds from the C-Class and E-Class.

It has some epic tech in it. Let’s take a look! 👀

- 12.3” driver display and 11.9” central display with third gen MBUX
- Third-party app integrations like Zoom, WebEx, TikTok, and even Angry Birds! (it’s VERY snappy)
- Stream on-demand or local video content with ZYNC
- Create customized routines (i.e. window automatically rolls down when you get home so you can get the mail)
- Option for 7-zone massage seats
- Option for BurmesterÒ 3D Surround Sound System with Dolby Atmos (ear-level speakers in both front seats - it sounds AMAZING)
- Sporty & seamless design with powerdomes and 18- to 20-inch wheels with rear axle steering
- Mild hybrid powertrains, supercharged with an electrifying second gen integrated starter-generator and a 48V on-board electrical system
- Four-cylinder, six-cylinder and there’s a plug-in hybrid down the line
- Frameless doors & two-part taillights
I could go on and on about this car. It’s absolutely gorgeous and it was an honor getting to shoot the behind the scenes of the new CLE world premiere. 🤗

#MercedesBenz #CLE #Coupe #Cabriolet

My favorite video frames & tech features from the @mercedesbenz #CLE launch 🤩👇🏻

1. The Displays
The central display has a six-degree incline towards the driver’s seat and a completely redesigned infotainment system. The 3rd generation of MBUX features 3rd party app integrations like Webex, Zoom or Angry birds!

2. The seven-zone massage seats
This one is self explanatory. It’s the ultimate luxury.

3. The Sound
You have the option for BurmesterÒ 3D surround sound system with Dolby Atmos which features 17 speakers. I cranked the volume as loud as I could… It sounded FANTASTIC. 
 
#MercedesBenz #CLE #Coupe #Cabriolet

New camera alert! Introducing the Sony a6700📸 I know we get A LOT of new Sony cameras 😅 but @sonyalpha hasn’t updated their photo first APS-C line since 2019!! (They’ve been focused on us video people whoops haha i.e. ZV-E10, FX30)

- 26.0MP back-illuminated Exmor R CMOS sensor
- Dedicated AI processor for subject recognition 
- Better image processing & AF 
- 759-point phase detection AF covering 93% of the image
- Bigger grip w/ NP-FZ100 battery
- Classic flippy screen
- Updated mode dials (they feel great)
- Up to 11fps w/ both mechanical & silent shutter w AF/AE tracking
- HEIF, lossless compress RAW

And just because it has that EVF doesn’t mean it’s lacking in the video department... (it’s basically a less expensive aps-c version of the Sony a7 iv?)

- 14+ stop dynamic range in movie recording
- Active Mode Stabilization
- 4k full pixel readout, 6k oversampling
- 4:2:2 10bit All-I
- 4K 120fps & 1080 240fps
- S-Cinetone, S-Log3, user assignable LUT’s
- AF Assist, breathing comp, focus map
- Ai based auto framing for movies

Ok so if you made it to the end of the caption please let me know why you think APS-C cameras ARE JUST AS GOOD AS FULL FRAME or let me know why you think FULL FRAME IS SUPERIOR OVER EVERYTHING tehe :)
